<br>
   I don't know, maybe my logic is flawed, but it sure makes a hell of a lot more sense to me than what your statement is inimating.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>They definately cast. You can use earth to root a mob without the pet ever swinging or even getting into melee range. Pull from a distance, send in the mudball before the mob gets very close. Pet will stop and *cast* its root spell; hit /pet back off as soon as it lands and there you have it--mob rooted and Jobober never even took a swing at it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
   As I stated above, I think the Earth pet does.  I am still not convinced that the air and water do.<br>
<br>
   Again, as I stated previously, if the Air and Water cast, then why is their base combat delay so much lower than the Earth and Epic, both of which are assumed to be casting.  Why is the Air and Water pet showing base combat delays comparable to other pets/warders that are known to not have procs/spells.<br>
<br>
