<br>
<br>
Water pets most definitely do cast, not proc.  Mine was slashing away with its ice DD from one side of the zone in area of HS to the other.  That's a good hundred feet or so, better than three times melee range.<br>
<br>
Pets most definitely WILL equip items beyond the first eight given them.  Mine had a full set of summoned plate, an elemental defender and two summoned daggers.  Of note is the fact that I gave my pet the daggers LAST, after the defender.  He didn't even try to equip the defender as a shield.  I suspect that any pet capable of dual wield will not equip a shield, but that's a guess. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wrathen@themagicianstower>Wrathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 3:49:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   STA</span><hr size=1> Well I didn't have much time to play with this as I wanted to but with 50-54 pets, sta didn't seem to affect them at all, however there are other factors that must be looked at with a lower dmg nuke.<br>
<br>
I chain nuked with shaman 81 dd spell to see how much dmg done per cast.  I made an alias to /report then /pet back off after each cast.<br>
<br>
Because of the regen of these guys at this level, and amount of base hps, its really hard to test it on them.<br>
<br>
However on 5 sessions without STA buff, then with, the nukes were almost identical in the amount of %health it took off per cast.  But if pets only get 40-80 hps from a lvl 44 sta spell, it would be extremely difficult to see a difference.<br>
<br>
I think it will be easier to test the lower level pets where hps are not as many and regen won't be as much a factor.  Also I am going to play with disease DoTs and see if I can find one that pretty much neutralizes the regen of the 50-54 pets, so the regen factor can be ruled out.<br>
<br>
I don't have any logs or numbers to post because I had to leave in a hurry this morning but I don't think anything too conclusive was found at this point anyways.<br>
<br>
As soon as I find something solid, I'll post logs and such in the pet forum. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lofwyr123>Lofwyr123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 7:38:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Back On Track!</span><hr size=1> Guys, get the thread back on track.<br>
<br>
Heres what I know about this:<br>
<br>
-Str has been shown to increase damage.  The question is whether it is affecting the ATK value or the DMG value.  If pets are damage capped it is even harder to see.<br>
<br>
-Dex does have an effect on the epic pets proc rate.  To my knowledge no other pet has an innate proc (does EoT?).  Using summon blade or fist it is possible to test this on other pets.  Spell lines that add procs may work different (does it add a cast or a proc, is there a conflict with a weapon having two procs that makes this so?), weapons may work different, no one knows.  Keep the test to an area we can be sure of.<br>
<br>
-Agi is near impossible to test, i forget how much agi it takes to noticably up ac but its a fair bit.  Some of the parses to test if the armor AC works could be repeated with buffs maybe?<br>
<br>
-Pets do hold more than 8 items, or if they have 8 new items are swapped out for old items.  Hand a pet 8 blades then a fist and see what it holds.  Try again with 10 blades.  This tells you if a pet only uses 8 items, or has an intenvtory of 8 items plus what its using (first test puts 2 in hand and 6 in invnetory, while second puts 2 in hand and 8 in inventory - see where the fists wind up in both cases).  NOTE- it is almost impossible to see if things are replaced as the items are not visable (weapons aside).  Also note that in my experience pets will sometimes use a new weapon, and sometimes not - is there a check to see what weapon is &quot;best&quot; that determines what it will use?<br>
<br>
-I have no idea on whether or not hp items, sta items and sta buffs affect pets.  It is pets dont have a sta value as an NPC and are simply assigned a base hp value.  Is there a STA debuff for mobs (not the neg sta items or potions)?  Not that i know of, makes sense if mobs dont have that value.  Plus if you debuffed a mobs sta its hp would go down in a percent fashion not as a add/subtract number value.  This seems both easier to code and seems to fit with what we are seeing - direct hp additions and subtractions work while sta doesnt.<br>
<br>
(edited for clarity) <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
